Class Level

  • java.lang.Object
    • Level

  • public class Level
extends java.lang.Object
    class Level

    Represents a three dimensional level in the game Flow3D.

    Uses a Cube object to store the information and set of Paths in the level.

    Version:
    1.6
    Author:
    Peter Stratton

    • Constructor Detail

      • Level

        public Level(int size,
             Point3I[] startPositionPairs)
        Constructor for Level

        Creates a new Level of a given size with a set of start point positions.

        Parameters:
        size - The size of the Cube this level represents.
        startPositionPairs - An array of start positions to use. Each pair will be given a different PathColor, up to all colors being used.

      • easy

        public static Level easy()
        Creates a new Level object set to the default "Tutorial" level.

        This is a simple 2x2x2 cube designed to teach the player that they need to fill in all spaces with the flow to pass the level.

        The start points PathType.START are hardcoded to their locations with their corresponding PathColor.

      • getFlowPath

        public java.util.LinkedList<Point3I> getFlowPath(PathColor color)
        Gets the flow path of a given PathColor through the Level.
        Parameters:
        color - The PathColor of the flow to get the flow of.
        Returns:
        a LinkedList of Point3Is that show where a color flows from and to. Will be null if there is no flow to be found.

      • getPreviousInFlow

        public Point3I getPreviousInFlow(Point3I location)
        Gets the location of the previous Path in a flow, if applicable.

      • hard

        public static Level hard()
        Creates a new Level object set to the default "hard" difficulty level.

        This is a simple 4x4x4 cube.

        The start points PathType.START are hardcoded to their locations with their corresponding PathColor.

      • isDrawable

        public boolean isDrawable(int x,
                          int y,
                          int z)
        Checks to see if a specific point is overwritable or not.

        If the Path at the given point is outside of the Level or is a PathType.START, then this will return false, and true otherwise.

        Parameters:
        x - The X location in the Level of the Path to check.
        y - The Y location in the Level of the Path to check.
        z - The Z location in the Level of the Path to check.
        Returns:
        whether the position is overwritable or not.

      • validLocation

        public boolean validLocation(int x,
                             int y,
                             int z)
        Checks to see if a position is a valid location within the Level. (Within it's indexes.)

        If all of the components of the given point are greater than or equal to zero and less than the size(), then this will return true, and false otherwise.

        Parameters:
        x - The X location in the Level of the Path to check.
        y - The Y location in the Level of the Path to check.
        z - The Z location in the Level of the Path to check.
        Returns:
        whether the position is within the Level or not.
